    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SDAP header configuration type casting in RRC DRB setup\n\n### Summary\nThe function `generateDRB_ASN1()` in `rrc_gNB_radio_bearers.c` was performing incorrect type casting when assigning SDAP header configuration values from the internal structure to the ASN.1 generated structure. This caused data corruption and misinterpretation of SDAP header presence/absence values downstream in the SDAP entity processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_radio_bearers.c`: Fixed type casting for `sdap_HeaderDL` and `sdap_HeaderUL` assignments in the `generateDRB_ASN1()` function by using proper `typeof` casting to ensure enum values are correctly preserved.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with multiple UEs establishing DRBs simultaneously, incorrect SDAP header configuration could lead to:\n- Segfaults in the SDAP entity when processing downlink data\n- Incorrect SDAP header insertion/removal causing packet corruption\n- UE RRC connection failures due to malformed RRC reconfiguration messages\n\nThe issue manifests most consistently when UEs request DRB setup with SDAP header enabled, where the `is_sdap_rx()` and `is_sdap_tx()` functions in `nr_sdap_entity.c` incorrectly evaluate the header configuration due to corrupted enum values.\n"
}